The paper proposes a method for calibrating camera-LiDAR systems for robotics, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves using 3D features and bundle adjustment, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also includes experiments with real data and visualizations, which are often associated with computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CVPR). Finally, the use of a closed-form solution and modified bundle adjustment suggests a focus on algorithmic development and optimization, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
